context.content:
Crab Town is a land of contrast. It is a beautiful country with 
wealthy people. However, while some people live in fancy 
houses and drive luxurious cars, many children are not so 
fortunate. There are those who suffer from malnutrition since 
the only food they have to eat is what they get out of garbage 
bins. Some of them do not even own a pair of shoes. These 
are the children who have never been to school since they 
have been abandoned by their parents. They are the ones 
who use the pavement for their pillows and the sky for a roof 
over their heads. They have no real home life and are crying 
out for help. Who will help them? [Adapted from

Common Entrance]
